{
  "texts": [
    "The relationship between R Hα index and I Hα index can be described by Equation (He et al, 2023) We evaluate the values of I Hα and R Hα indices for all the spectra in the MRS time-domain sample of solar-like stars employed in this work.",
    "The uncertainties of the I Hα and R Hα values (denoted by δI Hα and δR Hα, respectively) are also estimated by using the approach described in He et al (2023).",
    "In this work, when evaluating R Hα index, the spectra of the same stellar source use the same stellar atmospheric parameters of the source defined in Equation (1) to maintain consistency between the R Hα values of the co-source spectra.",
    "In the work of He et al (2023), when calculating R Hα, each spectrum uses its own stellar atmospheric parameter values provided in the MRS catalog, which is different from the scheme adopted in this work.",
    "Because the R Hα index reflects the absolute flux in the central band of the Hα line and hence is more physical than the I Hα index, the measure of Hα variability described in the next subsection is based on the R Hα index."
  ]
}